According to their study published in the journal Science, human beings do not want to be dropped at this type of competition, such as an auction on eBay, which is why they prefer to pay a price too high. 
This research has attempted to draw a diagram Neurological this kind of "game" using experimental auctions. 
A group of volunteers played the lottery, while another group took part in an auction playful, while in the process using a functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI), researchers analyzed the active brain areas experimental subjects. 
In both games, participants could make money, but during the auction which is essential to outbid a third, all located in the brainstem, called the striatum, moved to so intense at the loss of the game. 
This part of the brain, alongside several other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of "self-stimulation" of the nervous system. 
Therefore, according to the researchers, the rise in prices is due to the leak before the violent reaction in the striatum. 
In support of their theories, Members economists in this group of researchers have continued analysis of financial supervision. 
