While the third group had received the 15 dollars before the auction, but the group also lost the money, where they lost the auction. 
The difference between these two groups is that the emphasis was on with one victory, while at the other on failure. 
In proving the hypothesis neurologists, members of the team players "against failure" were willing to put higher than those made by the group and control group "for the victory." 
"These results can not be demonstrated by any existing economic theory. 
